14/09/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, leader of the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM), said on Tuesday (13 September) that his party and the Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) would hold talks on a new coalition deal ahead of next year's parliamentary elections. 
Buckovski said he is confident that an agreement would be announced shortly. 
He added that the SDSM and LDP would then jointly hold negotiations with another potential partner, VMRO-Macedonian. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 14/09/05)
